fields.name: Kanye West - College Drop Out
fields.description: The College Dropout is the debut studio album by American rapper and producer Kanye West. It was released on February 10, 2004, by Roc-A-Fella Records and Def Jam Recordings.

fields.name: MF DOOM - MM..Food
fields.description: Mm..Food (stylized in all caps) is the fifth studio album by British-American rapper/producer MF Doom, released by Rhymesayers in November 2004.

fields.name: Mac Miller - Circles
fields.description: Circles is the sixth and final studio album by American rapper and singer Mac Miller. It was released posthumously on January 17, 2020, by REMember Music and Warner Records, and was being worked on by Miller before his death in September 2018. Production was completed by Jon Brion.

fields.name: Freddie Gibbs - Alfredo
fields.description: Alfredo is a collaborative studio album by American rapper Freddie Gibbs and American hip hop producer The Alchemist. It was released on May 29, 2020, through Gibbs' own record label ESGN Records, as well as ALC Records and Empire Distribution.

fields.name: The XX - XX
fields.description: xx is the debut album by English indie pop band the xx. It was released on 14 August 2009 by Young Turks, an imprint label of XL Recordings. After signing a record contract with XL, the xx recorded the album from December 2008 to February 2009 at the label's in-house studio in London.

fields.name: Bombay Bicycle Club - Everything Else Has Gone Wrong
fields.description: Everything Else Has Gone Wrong is the fifth studio album by the British indie rock band Bombay Bicycle Club. It was released on 17 January 2020 by the band's own Mmm... Records imprint of Island Records, Caroline International and Arts & Crafts.

fields.name: Lucky Daye - Painted
fields.description: Painted is the debut studio album by American singer Lucky Daye. It was released on May 24, 2019, by Keep Cool Records and RCA Records.

fields.name: LCD Soundsystem - Sound of Silver
fields.description: Sound of Silver is the second studio album by American rock band LCD Soundsystem. The album was released jointly through DFA and Capitol Records in the United States and EMI elsewhere, first on March 12, 2007, in the United Kingdom.

fields.name: Miles Davis - Kind of Blue
fields.description: Kind of Blue is a studio album by American jazz trumpeter-composer Miles Davis. It was recorded on March 2 and April 22, 1959, at Columbia's 30th Street Studio in New York City, and released on August 17 of that year by Columbia Records.

fields.name: John Coltrane - Giant Steps
fields.description: Giant Steps is the fifth studio album by jazz musician John Coltrane as leader. It was released in February 1960 on Atlantic Records.

fields.name: Gil Scott Heron - Pieces of a Man
fields.description: Pieces of a Man is the first studio album by American vocalist Gil Scott-Heron. It was recorded in April 1971 at RCA Studios in New York City and released later that year by Flying Dutchman Records.

fields.name: Roy Ayers - Everybody Loves the Sunshine
fields.description: Everybody Loves the Sunshine is a studio album by Roy Ayers released under the Roy Ayers Ubiquity umbrella. It was released through Polydor Records in 1976. It peaked at number 51 on the Billboard 200 chart.
